### Check and Render Draft Mode Status in Server Component

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/draft-mode.mdx

Demonstrates how to check if Draft Mode is enabled using the isEnabled property and conditionally render content based on the Draft Mode status in a Server Component.

```typescript
import { draftMode } from 'next/headers'

export default async function Page() {
  const { isEnabled } = await draftMode()
  return (
    <main>
      <h1>My Blog Post</h1>
      <p>Draft Mode is currently {isEnabled ? 'Enabled' : 'Disabled'}</p>
    </main>
  )
}
```

