### Check Cookie Existence

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

Checks if a cookie exists using the cookies().has() method. Returns a boolean value indicating whether a cookie with the specified name is present.

```APIDOC
## GET Check Cookie Existence

### Description
Checks if a cookie with the specified name exists using the cookies().has() method. This method must be called within a Server Component or Server Action.

### Method
GET (read operation)

### Endpoint
Server-side operation via `(await cookies()).has()`

### Parameters
#### Method Parameters
- **name** (string) - Required - The name of the cookie to check

### Usage Example
```typescript
const cookieStore = await cookies()
const hasCookie = cookieStore.has('theme')
```

### Response
#### Return Value
- **boolean** - true if cookie exists, false otherwise

#### Response Example
```typescript
true  // if cookie named 'theme' exists
false // if cookie named 'theme' does not exist
```
```

