### Authorization Check in Server Action with Role Verification

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/authentication.mdx

Implements security checks in a Next.js Server Action by verifying the user session and validating their role before allowing mutation operations. Returns early if the user lacks required permissions, treating Server Actions with the same security rigor as public API endpoints. Demonstrates both TypeScript and JavaScript patterns.

```typescript
'use server'
import { verifySession } from '@/app/lib/dal'

export async function serverAction(formData: FormData) {
  const session = await verifySession()
  const userRole = session?.user?.role

  // Return early if user is not authorized to perform the action
  if (userRole !== 'admin') {
    return null
  }

  // Proceed with the action for authorized users
}
```

