### Implement get() method in cache handler

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/cacheHandlers.mdx

Implement the get() method to retrieve cache entries from storage and check expiration. The method takes a cache key and soft tags as parameters, checks if the entry has expired based on the revalidate time, and returns the entry or undefined if not found or expired.

```javascript
const cacheHandler = {
  async get(cacheKey, softTags) {
    const entry = cache.get(cacheKey)
    if (!entry) return undefined

    // Check if expired
    const now = Date.now()
    if (now > entry.timestamp + entry.revalidate * 1000) {
      return undefined
    }

    return entry
  },
}
```

