### Check draftMode and Conditional Data Fetching in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/draft-mode.mdx

Implements a page component that checks draftMode().isEnabled to determine whether to fetch data from a draft or production endpoint. The getData function retrieves the isEnabled status and routes requests accordingly. This approach enables live draft previews while maintaining performance for production builds.

```typescript
// page that fetches data
import { draftMode } from 'next/headers'

async function getData() {
  const { isEnabled } = await draftMode()

  const url = isEnabled
    ? 'https://draft.example.com'
    : 'https://production.example.com'

  const res = await fetch(url)

  return res.json()
}

export default async function Page() {
  const { title, desc } = await getData()

  return (
    <main>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{desc}</p>
    </main>
  )
}
```

