### Proxy Authentication Check with Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/backend-for-frontend.mdx

Implements a proxy handler that validates authentication before allowing requests to proceed. Uses the isAuthenticated helper function to check request credentials and returns a 401 JSON response if authentication fails. Supports path matching via config.matcher to target specific API routes.

```typescript
import { isAuthenticated } from '@lib/auth'

export const config = {
  matcher: '/api/:function*',
}

export function proxy(request: Request) {
  if (!isAuthenticated(request)) {
    return Response.json(
      { success: false, message: 'authentication failed' },
      { status: 401 }
    )
  }
}
```

