### Verify User Session with `verifySession` in Next.js DAL

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/authentication.mdx

This function verifies the user's session by decrypting a cookie and checking for a valid `userId`. If the session is invalid, it redirects the user to the login page. It uses React's `cache` API to memoize the return value, preventing redundant checks during a React render pass and enhancing performance.

```tsx
import 'server-only';

import { cookies } from 'next/headers';
import { decrypt } from '@/app/lib/session';
import { cache } from 'react'; // Assuming cache is imported from 'react'
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation'; // Assuming redirect is imported from 'next/navigation'

export const verifySession = cache(async () => {
  const cookie = cookies().get('session')?.value;
  const session = await decrypt(cookie);

  if (!session?.userId) {
    redirect('/login');
  }

  return { isAuth: true, userId: session.userId };
});
```

